g.text: Kim Kitsuragi: "One more thing before we do..." He glances at the booth again. "We don't have to talk to them immediately. We can walk right past them, continue with our business."
Authority: Good. A power move. *Purposefully* concentrate on something else first.
Reaction Speed: Yeah -- streetwise. Zoom right past, do it on your own terms.
Kim Kitsuragi: "And one more thing..." He pulls the black plastic over the dead man's face, then looks at you. "This was *very* good work, detective."
Interfacing: Oh well -- we'll get the armoured boots in another lifetime.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Looks like we can get to work at once. The Union muscle turned up." He points to the mess hall doors. "They look rowdy. We should talk to them."
Kim Kitsuragi: "And the big one," he squints his eyes, studying the men in the mess hall, "must be Hardie himself..."
Rhetoric: The lieutenant is downplaying his contribution -- he got up before sunrise to get this done. And now he's quite pleased with himself for taking care of the gruesome business so efficiently.
Kim Kitsuragi: He points to the mess hall doors. "The Union muscle finally turned up, and they look rowdy. We need to talk to them."
Kim Kitsuragi: "That would just escalate tensions. No captain would sign off on it. Solving one murder isn't worth a conflict between the RCM and the Débardeurs' Union."
Kim Kitsuragi: "In fact, even the *death* of two detectives might not warrant an all-out war. So let's keep a cool head, okay?"
You: "Are these the men Garte told us about yesterday?"
You: "Why do we need to talk to them?"
You: "There are so many of them. Maybe we should call in reinforcements?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I've got some good news." The lieutenant smiles. "I took care of the body. The thought of him decomposing in my MC wouldn't let me sleep."
You: "I don't know if I was ready to let him go..."
Composure: He won't even *acknowledge* the stolen boots you're wearing. For him, they don't exist. You'll have to bring it up yourself, later -- *if* you dare.
Empathy: He kind of wishes you'd acknowledged his contribution, but you've missed your opportunity now.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Men who drink beer for breakfast. I have no doubt these are the Hardie boys Evrart told us about, the ones who *keep the peace* around here."
Logic: But... aren't you *curious* to know what they have to say about the murder?
Kim Kitsuragi: "They're in no hurry to leave -- they think they own the place... Anyway, I leave that choice to you. Whatever you decide is fine by me."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Everything points to the Dockworkers' Union: the tracks in the mud, the circumstances in Martinaise, my preliminary information..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Which may, of course, all be wrong. But we still need to talk to them -- and it won't be easy."
Kim Kitsuragi: "A lot of things point to the Dockworkers' Union: the circumstances in Martinaise, my preliminary information. Hmm, actually..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm just glad he's gone. We have other matters to attend to."
Kim Kitsuragi: "One loose thread less to worry about -- and one big problem to replace it." He crosses something out.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Well, he's in processing now. We have other matters to attend to."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Looks like we can get to work at once. The Union muscle turned up." He points to the mess hall doors. "They look rowdy. We should talk to them."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm just glad he's gone. We have other matters to attend to."
Interfacing: Oh well -- we'll get the armoured boots in another lifetime.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We can't be sure of course -- Evrart may have lied to us. He definitely has an agenda of his own. Either way, we need to interview them. And it won't be easy."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I completely forgot." He looks at his notes. "Sorry, I had a rough night's sleep. It's them, by the looks of it -- loud and nasty, just like the manager said."
Kim Kitsuragi: "...that's not *a lot* of things. We should have dug up more yesterday. Still, we need to talk to them. And it won't be easy."
Half Light: He's not exaggerating about that mortal danger. Just calmly factoring it in. Your fists clench and your pulse rises uncomfortably.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Well, he's in processing now. We have other matters to attend to."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I mean ungovernable. Martinaise isn't exactly enthusiastic about the RCM being here. They prefer to be *policed* by the Union -- these men here..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "This is clearly the Union's *peacekeeping* force Evrart told us about. The one he said hanged our victim."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Men who drink beer for breakfast? There's talk of an armed wing of the Union called *the Hardie boys*, who are responsible for said *policing*. I think it's them."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Everything points to the Dockworkers' Union: the *belt* used for hanging him, the circumstances in Martinaise, my preliminary information..."
"Everything points to the Dockworkers' Union: the belt used for hanging him, tracks in the mud, the circumstances in Martinaise, my preliminary information..."
